value.title: Cash-strapped Trump campaign awaits a bailout from big donors
value.excerpt: Preserve America, a new super PAC backing the president, is planning another $25 million ad blitz attacking Joe Biden.

value.title: Biden blasts AG Barr for comments comparing coronavirus restrictions to slavery
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden went after Attorney General Bill Barr during a CNN Town Hall Thursday evening, calling Barr’s linking of coronavirus restrictions to slavery, “outrageous.”

value.title: Biden is asked if he benefited from White privilege
value.excerpt: During a CNN town hall in Pennsylvania, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden addresses how "the talk" within Black families about police interaction will be different under his administration, and if he believes he's benefited off White privilege.

value.title: Pence's former top aide says Trump called coronavirus 'a good thing' because he didn't like shaking hands with 'disgusting' supporters
value.excerpt: Olivia Troye said Trump was primarily concerned with the economy and his reelection and undermined the task force's pandemic response.

value.title: Fact check: Fake article from 2015 quoting Donald Trump resurfaces
value.excerpt: The article reports Trump the candidate was in Indianapolis and disparaged African Americans at an event. The claim is false; that never happened.

value.title: Biden floats fining people for not wearing a mask on federal property
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden offered little clarity on whether he could and would introduce a national mask mandate should he win the White House on Nov. 3.

value.title: Democrats ramp up virtual campaign with NC ‘visits’ from Kamala Harris, Jill Biden | Charlotte Observer
value.excerpt: President Trump is making regular stops in NC and the Biden campaign is countering with virtual events from high-profile Democrats.

value.title: Trump plans panel to promote 'patriotic education' in appeal to conservative base
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump said on Thursday he planned to establish a commission to promote "patriotic education" in the United States, taking issue with efforts to highlight the United States' history of slavery and racism.

value.title: READ: Judge's ruling criticizing Trump and DeJoy for USPS changes
value.excerpt: Federal Judge Stanley Bastian criticized President Donald Trump and Postmaster General Louis DeJoy and issued a nationwide order blocking some recent changes that slowed down mail services.

value.title: Former top U.S. Catholic official: There are ‘morally grave’ reasons to vote for Biden
value.excerpt: John Carr, longtime Catholic adviser who opposed abortion, say he will vote for Joe Biden despite the Democrat’s support for existing abortion laws.

value.title: Pence dismisses ex-aide voting for Biden as 'disgruntled employee'
value.excerpt: Vice President Pence on Thursday dismissed a former aide who said she would vote for Democratic nominee Joe Biden, calling her a “disgruntled employee” playing politics.

value.title: Trump rails against the 'liberal indoctrination of America's youth' in latest culture war salvo
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump railed against what he described as "the liberal indoctrination of America's youth" during a Constitution Day speech on Thursday, marking his latest attempt to inflame the culture wars raging in America ahead of the election.

value.title: Twitter public policy director decamps for Biden transition team
value.excerpt: Twitter public policy director Carlos Monje's exact position on the transition team was not immediately clear.

value.title: FBI Director Wray says Russia is actively interfering in 2020 election to 'denigrate' Biden
value.excerpt: FBI Director Christopher Wray said Thursday that Russia has been "very active" in its efforts to influence US elections, with the primary goal being to "denigrate" Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden.

value.title: Pennsylvania Supreme Court election rulings are big wins for Biden
value.excerpt: The Pennsylvania Supreme Court on Thursday removed the Green Party candidate from the 2020 presidential ballot and cleared the way for local officials to start sending out absentee ballots to voters.

value.title: Sen. Ron Johnson won't travel with Trump after exposure to individual who tested positive for Covid
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Ron Johnson of Wisconsin will no longer be traveling with President Donald Trump on Thursday after learning that he was exposed to an individual who tested positive for Covid-19, a spokesman for the senator announced.

value.title: Biden tells Democratic senators he takes 'nothing for granted' during caucus call
value.excerpt: The Democratic presidential nominee called into the Senate Democrats’ daily caucus meeting Thursday and reassured members that he'll hit the trail in the final stretch of the campaign — particularly in key swing states.

value.title: Report: Scott Walker helping Mike Pence in debate preparations
value.excerpt: The Washington Post reported Walker is "serving as Pence’s foil in practice sessions, effectively playing the role" of U.S. Sen. Kamala Harris.

value.title: CNN to host first 'drive-in town hall' with Biden on Thursday
value.excerpt: CNN says it will host a "drive-in town hall" with Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden on Thursday night, which the network calls "the latest adaptation to campaigning during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Joe Biden's dangerous view of 'normalcy'

value.title: Identity politics can help Biden win in November
value.excerpt: American attitudes have changed dramatically over the past 4 years, and appeals for racial equity can motivate Democrats to vote.

value.title: Biden Under Pressure To Unveil List of Potential Court Picks
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is resisting calls from President Donald Trump and even some fellow Democrats to release his list of potential Supreme Court picks seven months after he pledged to name

value.title: GOP growing more indifferent with Trump controversies as election nears
value.excerpt: Public health experts reacted with alarm after President Donald Trump held an indoor rally with thousands of maskless supporters at a packed arena in Nevada amid the deadly coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: ‘SNL’: Which Actors Played Joe Biden Before Jim Carrey?
value.excerpt: Actor Jim Carrey will take on the role of presidential nominee Joe Biden on Saturday Night Live this season. The announcement may have come as a surprise to some fans as Biden has been skillfully played by other actors on the series in the past.

value.title: Asked about Biden criticism, UK says N.Irish peace deal not at risk
value.excerpt: British junior health minister Edward Argar said on Thursday that he did not believe the 1998 Northern Irish peace deal was at risk, responding to criticism from U.S. Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden.
